net.hudup.core.alg

Interface MemoryBasedRecommender

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Alg, AlgRemoteTask, Exportable, Inspectable, MemoryBasedAlg, Recommender, RecommenderRemoteTask, java.io.Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    MemoryBasedCF
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MemoryBasedCFAbstract, MemoryBasedRecommenderAbstract, NeighborCF, NeighborCF2d, NeighborCFItemBased, NeighborCFUserBased

    public interface MemoryBasedRecommender
extends Recommender, MemoryBasedAlg
    Two typical inherited interfaces of Recommender are MemoryBasedRecomender and ModelBasedRecommender which in turn are interfaces for memory-based recommendation algorithm and model-based recommendation algorithm. As a convention, this interface is called memory-based recommender. This memory-based recommender makes recommendation tasks directly on dataset represented by Dataset class. It often stores rating matrix in memory. Recommendation tasks are executed in memory. Memory-based recommender is often simpler than model-based recommender.
    Version:
    10.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen
